<br>
He nodded to Hecate, having proved himself a worthy opponent she would probably move on the find more lucrative a sparring partner. Quickly, to waste no time, Apollo dived back into the deepest recesses of the battle.<br>
<br>
Eventually Apollo had made it to the front lines, where he found Hypnos. He stood there before Hypnos, the air blowing his golden locks around, the battle still going on inback of him. It was as if all sound was drained from the fighting as Apollo spoke to Hypnos:<br>
<br>
&quot;It is a shame. That as &quot;divine characters&quot; we must lower ourselves to such things. Such primative ways of putting an argument to rest. But pride, the very thing that drives such a war, is one of the brain's most primitive functions. I hope that one day, soon , we can move on from this opprobrium, for that is what it is. It's disgraceful the way we act out here today.&quot;<br>
<br>
He paused, as if deciding how to make his next move.<br>
<br>
&quot;But a war is nothing without battles. And no battle goes unfought under such circumstances. So come on Hypnos&quot;<br>
<br>
A smirk rode across his face as he pulled his sword in front of him, his eyes glazing over with anticipation.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's Dance.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/21/01 3:28:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=146>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~War~</span><hr size=1> Varia reaches out with the tip of her sword and pops the bubble. Sucking the bubble into her mouth, she chews it up like gum and spits it back in Hypnos' face, globbing him right in the eye! {hehe} <p><html> <font face="Signet Roundhand ATT"> Queen Varia </font> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/21/01 3:36:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=147>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alastor ~-Versus-~ Poseidon</span><hr size=1> ::He pushed down on Alastors blade as the sounds of battle filled his ears. He smiled seeing Alastor struggling and falling to his knee. Poseidon put his weight into the push and then his smile turned into a grin as he lost his momentum and Alastor drew himself upright once more. He nearly lost his balance as his trident was forced down to the ground. Tumbling forward Alastor's gauntlet struck him on the jaw. Poseidon's head snapped to the side and his teeth clenched as a small stream of blood came from the flesh that tore on the inside of his mouth and dripped off his lips. In a