<br>
 Her hand went silently to the blade at her thigh, pulling it slowly from the sheath, into the air. The black blade made no flicker no sight, no sound. Nothing could be detected of the assassins movements. The last known thing would have been her ascending to the tree.<br>
<br>
 Once focused and prepared, Dawn pulled back and launched the knife into the air. The blade rotated at a high velocity, aimed almost perfectly for Hecate's shoulder blade.<br>
<br>
 This was a somewhat stupid move, Dawn realized, once she had let the weapon leave. And with that had retreated back to the ground, and into the woods. She would be out of sight before Hecate could see who through the weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/21/01 6:46:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=153>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .·:*¨¨*:·.Hecate Vs Apollo.·:*¨¨*:·.</span><hr size=1> Apollo's jaw clenched as the vines wrapped around his body, embracing him in their organic might. He struggled to no avail. He felt the blood being squeezed from different parts of his body.<br>
<br>
Pain. Sharp. His eyes wandered to the arrow that found itself so neatly embedded within his flesh. Enough of these games. Apollo's golden aura began to glow. Now this aura would normally be useless, unless it was the aura of Apollo, whose aura was of the sun. As the golden light grew bigger and brighter the vines began to burn, slowly dying and turning into brittle, breakable twigs.<br>
<br>
Snap, crackle, pop. The twigs around him broke. He raised his arm and pulled the arrow from his shoulder, who by some mishap or another, hand'nt found its way all the way into his shoulder. Apollo lifted his arms, swinging it in circles several times to get his arm back in working order.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nice move.&quot; Apollo smirked pulling his sword from its sheath. He placed his hand on the edge of the blade and ran his finger over it. His eyes lingered on the ghostly figure of Hecate. Suddenly Apollo lunged at Hecate with all his speed, lifting the sword over his shoulder. He quickly brought the sword down towards the shoulder of Hecate.<br>
<br>
